result.execSummary:
The defendant Andrew A Newton was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery by Prisoners [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.20(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Court orders the fines, costs, and restitution in this file shall be paid from all earnings received in accordance with prison policy, not to exceed 25% of gross during the term of initial confinement. If any fines, costs, and/or restitution remain outstanding at the end of the initial confinement portion of this sentence, then the remaining shall be paid directly to the Waushara Co Clerk of Circuit Court or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges granted to the extent Defendant has the ability to exercise work release.
Consecutive to: Any sentence Defendant is currently serving.
No DNA sample and/or surcharge is assessed as Defendant previously provided the same through another felony conviction.

records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 11:05 AM: Defendant Andrew A Newton in court with attorney Michael Ross Blum.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Per Atty Blum:  Defendant requests the matter be set for jury trial.  Per DA:  State was under the impression that matter was resolved and would go to sentencing today.  Victim present.  Defendant has a release date sometime this week from RGCI and Court will need to readdress bond today.  Atty Blum confirms that release date is within a few days and will be on ES.  Def will resume employment and will retain his own private counsel.  The Court:  Risk of flight issue is paramount based upon allegations of Complaint.  $5000 Cash Bond ordered with all previously established conditions as ordered and will include no contact with both complainants in this action.  Off Record @ 11:08 AM to allow for Def to confer with his counsel.    Back of Record @ 11:17 AM:  Joint Resolution recited by DA.  Counsel and Def confirm recital.  Terms of bifurcated SEH explained.  Maximum terms of imprisonment recited with Repeater component.    Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  No impairment on proceeding today.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea Ct 2 w/Repeater Enh:  NC  Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  Ct No 1 DRI.  Victim present (Off T. Wilson) and makes statement prior to SEH.  No further argument by DA.  Argument by Atty Blum.  Statement by Def:  Yes.  The Court:  Court imposes 1 yr WCJ consecutive to any sentence currently being served - GT credit - no TS credit - Huber Privileges if can be exercised; Court Costs plus DNA Surcharge ordered by the Court - Court orders the fines, costs, and restitution in this file shall be paid from all earnings received in accordance with prison policy, not to exceed 25% of gross during the term of initial confinement. If any fines, costs, and/or restitution remain outstanding at the end of the initial confinement portion of this sentence, then the remaining shall be paid directly to COC in accordance with repayment policy.   DNA Sample previously provided thru Calumet Co case.  DA makes statement as to possible discharge from RGCI in light of Co Jail SEH - it is unknown if Def will remain at RGCI or remanded to WCJ - will be determined by DOC as to where this sentence will be served.  Appeal Rights Given.

records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 10:03 AM: Defendant Andrew A Newton in court, appearing via telephone from RGCI with attorney Jayme L. Lehman, appearing via telephone.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court has been presented with a request by Atty Lehman to withdraw and wishes to formally address with the Defendant.  Notes for the record that this is the second request by Def for withdrawal.  Per Atty Lehman an irretreivable breakdown has occurred in communications with Def.  Court advises Def of this second request by counsel to withdraw.  Statement by Def as to withdrawal requests.  Court advises Def that he would again need to apply to SPD for a 3rd appointment and there is a limit to SPD appointing counsel.  If SPD reaches a point where no further attorneys would be appointed, Def would be responsible for his own counsel.  The Court will not find the Def eligible for Court Appointment.  Court will grant Atty Lehman's request to withdraw as counsel of record.   Atty Lehman to notify SPD of her withdrawal.  STC adjourned as requested while Court awaits appointment of subsequent counsel.  Status conference scheduled for May 24, 2016 at 09:55 am.
